        "company": "Hofy",
        "company_url": "https://www.hofy.co.uk/",
        "location": "EU-TimeZones (GMT+3 to GMT-1)",
        "title": "Fullstack Lead Engineer - Fully Remote",
        "description": "<p><strong>Fullstack Lead Engineer – Fully Remote</strong>\nSalary range – £60,000 – £100,000 per year + equity based on experience and fit</p>\n<p>This is a unique opportunity for a Fullstack lead/senior developer who is highly proficient with Node and React to become the lead developer of a fully funded and growing UK startup. You’ll be working from home (or anywhere else), earning £60K to £100K/year + equity based on experience and fit.</p>\n<p>Work from home trends have ebbed and flowed over the past years, but this trend has been dramatically accelerated following Coronavirus. The working from home trend shows no signs of slowing down. Hofy aims to let organizations provide home offices to their team while remaining compliant with health and safety and tax regulations. Organizations can pre-approve products from Hofy’s catalog and invite their team members to browse and order from their private Hofy store-front. Hofy then delivers and responds to service/replacement requests on all of the items.</p>\n<p>Our magic happens by combining great UX with a smart Backend that apart for managing the virtual stores, distributes, and assigns the jobs efficiently among our network of distributed technicians.  That’s why we need to build a great engineering team.</p>\n<p>We are running on GCP with a tech-stack of Mongo, Express, React &amp; Node.</p>\n<p><strong>You will</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Be our lead developer reporting directly to the COO</li>\n<li>Become part of the Hofy family</li>\n<li>Own the implementation of our product</li>\n<li>Contribute to the product strategy</li>\n<li>Build the technical and development processes infrastructure</li>\n<li>Turning the product strategy into actionable objectives</li>\n<li>Working with product management to optimize quality vs speed</li>\n<li>Delegating work to the other members of the engineering team</li>\n<li>Set the tone of how our product will look like under the hood</li>\n<li>Be 80% hands-on (coding and architecture) while at the same time building and leading our engineering team</li>\n<li>This is a role with significant responsibility and impact on the company</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>You’d be a great fit if you ❤️</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Are a high-performing Fullstack developer (&amp; lead) who is highly proficient across the MERN stack</li>\n<li>Are enthusiastic about joining an early-stage (fully funded!) startup</li>\n<li>Passionate about being part of the remote-work revolution by building services for remote-teams</li>\n<li>Want to keep your strong hands-on abilities while combining leadership</li>\n<li>Love building things from scratch (products as well as teams)</li>\n<li>Spent some time in a company with strong software development processes culture\n** CICD, Code Reviews, Unit and Integration Testing</li>\n<li>Spent some time in a smaller startup company where you have learned about startup product development (vs corporate)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Bonus points if you 🏆</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Were a CTO/founder of a startup company</li>\n<li>Have production experience with GCP or AWS</li>\n<li>Have experience working in a distributed team(s) environment</li>\n<li>Have experience building high-performing distributed team(s)</li>\n<li>Used to own a 24/7 SaaS product, running on a major vendor cloud</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Competitive Equity</li>\n<li>Distributed &amp; Flexible Work Arrangements</li>\n<li>Full home-office setup</li>\n<li>Inclusive Work Environment</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://bit.ly/2YIHa5G\">Click here</a> to read the full job description and Apply</p>\n",
        "how_to_apply": "<p>Apply here - <a href=\"https://bit.ly/2YIHa5G\">https://bit.ly/2YIHa5G</a></p>\n",
