        "description": "<p><strong>As C++ Software Engineer</strong> you are part of our Software Engineering Team and will heavily contribute to the integration of the holoride technology into series-production vehicles. Given your role as holoride advocate and technical peer for our global partners, your professional experience will ensure to bring holoride from the concept stage to integration and production readiness, respectively. You will be building a framework using your C++ coding skills that will aim to facilitate all technical requirements for our automotive OEM partners. Furthermore, you will be maintaining and extending the holoride localization technology in our ecosystem.</p>\n<p><strong>What you’ll bring along</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Strong technical development experience in modern C++</li>\n<li>Experience in working with agile methods</li>\n<li>Independent learning and collaborative problem solving</li>\n<li>Good written and verbal English language skills</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Bonus qualifications</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience in Android and/or iOS development</li>\n<li>Experience with Conan and CMake</li>\n<li>Experience with Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What we offer</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>The possibility to work on one of the hottest topics in the current tech scene and cooperate with global brands</li>\n<li>The opportunity to grow professionally, take on responsibility for your own projects and ideas and see the immediate impact of your work</li>\n<li>The flexibility in designing your preferred working style — either in the office or remotely from home</li>\n<li>A fair and competitive market salary</li>\n<li>Become part of an international, ambitious and diverse team of experts and highly engaged peers</li>\n<li>Doing whatever possible to make you really fall in love with your job</li>\n<li>To challenge yourself and the status quo of what’s currently possible in in-car entertainment</li>\n<li>A spacious, modern, and fun office in the heart of Munich offering lots of free amenities</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What we do</strong></p>\n<p>holoride is a tech-entertainment startup working at the intersection of mobility and Extended Reality (XR). By synchronizing the contents of VR/XR glasses with external influences such as acceleration, steering, and navigational data, we are creating a never before seen passenger experience. We are changing in-car entertainment forever. Find out more <a href=\"https://youtu.be/DTSwWV7l8b4\">here</a> and visit us on <a href=\"http://linkedin.com/company/holoride\">LinkedIn</a></p>\n",
